div.div: In the late 19th century, the British Empire nobility reigns while its working class suffers at their hands. Sympathetic to their plight, William James Moriarty wants to topple it all. Frustrated by the systemic inequity, Moriarty strategizes to fix the entire nation. Not even consulting detective Sherlock Holmes can stand in his way. It's time for crime to revolutionize the world! (Source: Funimation) Note: The first episode received an early screening on September 21st, 2020. The regular TV broadcast started on October 11th, 2020.
Kyoukai no Kanata: I'LL BE HERE - Mirai-hen
Action, Drama, Fantasy, Romance, Slice of Life, Supernatural
This is the second part of a two-part movie. The story takes place one year after the TV series.
Iinazuke ga Dekita to Omottara, Sono Iinazuke ga Gakkou de Yuumeina [Akuyaku Reijou] Dattan Dakedo, Dosureba Ii?

One Saturday morning, his father told him something shocking, “You have a fiancee."

Hiroyuki Higashikujo is a second-year high school boy. He goes between home and school without a girlfriend, but he is living a peaceful life without any complaints. Or, he was supposed to be, until all the marriage talk went on and on without regard to Hiroyuki...... and they were told that they are going to live together! His bride-to-be is a perfect young lady who goes to the same high school as Hiroyuki and she is smart, beautiful, and atheletic, too!

"I'm telling you, you don't have the right to refuse," she says with a face cold as absolute zero. This is the famous “villainess” of the school…!?

(Source: Dash Bunko, translated)
